<h1 class="title">Project Overview</h1>

<div class="app-overview">
  <p>
    This Role-Based Access Control (RBAC) project is a secure and scalable solution for managing user authentication, authorization, and roles in a web application. This project demonstrates core concepts of modern web security and provides a practical example of access control in action.
  </p>

  <h2>Key Features</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><b>User Authentication:</b> Register and log in securely using email and password.</li>
    <li><b>Role-Based Access Control:</b> Assign roles to users, including Admin, Moderator, and Client.</li>
    <li><b>Content Management:</b> Moderators can manage their own content while admins oversee all content.</li>
    <li><b>Activity Logs:</b> Detailed logs track user actions for security and auditing purposes.</li>
    <li><b>Admin Panel:</b> Manage users, view profiles, and update roles (accessible to Admins).</li>
    <li><b>Session Persistence:</b> Sessions are securely stored using MongoDB.</li>
    <li><b>Flash Messages:</b> Provide feedback to users, including errors and success notifications.</li>
    <li><b>Custom Styling:</b> Modern, clean design for better user experience.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Technologies Used</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><b>Backend:</b> Node.js with Express.js framework</li>
    <li><b>Database:</b> MongoDB with Mongoose ORM</li>
    <li><b>Authentication:</b> Passport.js for local authentication</li>
    <li><b>View Engine:</b> EJS for templating</li>
    <li><b>CSS:</b> Custom styling for an attractive and responsive UI</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>How to Get Started</h2>
  <ol>
    <li>
      <b>Register an Account:</b> Click on the "Register" link in the navigation bar to create an account.
    </li>
    <li>
      <b>Log In:</b> Use your email and password to log in. Depending on your role, you'll gain access to different features.
    </li>
    <li>
      <b>Explore:</b> If you are an Admin, visit the Admin Panel to manage users, and view detailed logs of user activities for auditing. Moderators and Clients will have access to their respective features.
    </li>
    <li>
      <b>Content Management:</b> Moderators can create, and view their own content, while Admins have full oversight.
    </li>
  </ol>
</div>

